persitions%20need%20to%20be%20laid%20to%20rest.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20quite%20literally%2C%20as%20I%20finally%20decided%20to%20make%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-to-make-a-will-without-a-lawyer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elast%20will%20and%20testament%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20in%20my%2050s%20and%20know%20this%20would%20be%20a%20no-brainer%20for%20most%20people.%20But%20I%20never%20married%20or%20had%20children%2C%20so%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprotect-my-assets-income-streams-getting-will-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emaking%20a%20will%3C%2Fa%3E%20never%20seemed%20like%20something%20I%20had%20to%20do.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20%26quot%3Bjinx%26quot%3B%20my%20life%2C%20but%20I%20realized%20that%20after%20working%20so%20many%20years%20to%20obtain%20the%20things%20I%20wanted%2C%20it%20seemed%20rational%20enough%20to%20want%20to%20ensure%20that%20they%20go%20to%20a%20good%20place%20when%20I%20am%20no%20longer%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20admittedly%20put%20this%20task%20off%20for%20a%20while.%20Apparently%2C%20I%20am%20not%20alone.%20A%202020%20Gallup%20poll%20found%20that%20fewer%20than%20half%20of%20adults%20in%20the%20US%20have%20a%20will.%20I%20know%20that%20I%20feared%20making%20one%2C%20because%20it%20meant%20I'd%20be%20accepting%20my%20own%20mortality.%20I'm%20glad%20I've%20recently%20come%20around%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221a9de037-d0e0-473d-a4bb-98ee7a0a9618%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFiguring%20out%20the%20process%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20some%20research%2C%20I%20learned%20that%20as%20a%20teacher%2C%20I%20am%20eligible%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-much-does-it-cost-to-make-a-will%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efree%20will%20preparation%20service%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20contacted%20the%20legal%20agency%20listed%20in%20my%20benef