20she%20casually%20mentioned%20that%20the%20bulk%20of%20her%20donations%20came%20from%20people%20who%20left%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-inheritance-can-destroy-family-be-gift-estate-planning-attorney-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eportion%20of%20their%20estate%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20nonprofit%20in%20their%20wills.%20I%20decided%20to%20do%20the%20same.%20I%20loved%20my%20cats%20more%20than%20I%20could%20imagine%2C%20and%20the%20thought%20of%20helping%20other%20animals%20while%20they%20waited%20to%20find%20their%20forever%20homes%20filled%20me%20with%20joy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquestions-to-ask-when-hiring-estate-planning-attorney-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elegal%20firm's%3C%2Fa%3E%20number%20and%20made%20an%20appointment%20to%20work%20on%20my%20will.%20The%20idea%20still%20frightened%20me%2C%20but%20I%20had%20come%20to%20realize%20the%20beauty%20of%20passing%20on%20things%20to%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20headed%20to%20the%20firm's%20office%20in%20downtown%20Brooklyn.%20It%20was%20pure%20old%20school%20aesthetics%2C%20with%20manila%20files%20piling%20out%20of%20every%20corner.%20The%20leather%20chairs%20were%20worn%20and%20frayed%2C%20but%20the%20people%20were%20warm%20and%20lovely.%20A%20lawyer%20came%20out%20and%20patiently%20explained%20everything%20to%20me.%20When%20he%20brought%20up%20my%20intended%20donation%20to%20the%20ASPCA%2C%20we%20talked%20about%20my%20own%20cats%20for%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20which%20helped%20me%20feel%20comfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20what%20seemed%20like%20only%20minutes%2C%20I%20signed%20and%20initialized%20the%20documents%20and%20took%20my%20complimentary%20pen%20home.%20It%20felt%20different%20in%20a%20way%20I%20couldn't%20quite%20put%20my%20finger%20on.%20There's%20a%20feeling%20you%20have%20when%20you're%20growing%20up%20and%20have%20a%20landmark%20birthday%20or%20celebration%2C%20and%20you're%20so%20excited%20and%20feel%20so%20alive.%20This%20was%20sort%20of%20the%20same%20feeling%2C%20but%20at%20the%20other%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225cdbbb6a-e472-454b-ad11-8920514b89d9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20my%20will%20made%20me%20feel%20empowered%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20part%20of%20me%20was%20already%20reminiscing%20about%20my%20life%20so%20far%2C%20and%20for%20a%20moment%2C%20I%20thought%20about%20what%20the%20world%20might%20be%20like%20when%20I%20was%20gone.%20I%20felt%20relieved%20knowing%20that%20people%20I%20loved%20would%20be%20able%20to%20enjoy%20some%20of%20the%20physical%20possessions%20I%20held%20dearly%2C%20and%20I%20smiled%2C%20thinking%20about%20the%20animals%20and%20their%20future%20owners%20and%20how%20my%20donation%20would%20help%20bring%20them%20together.%20And%20then%20I%20exhaled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20preparing%20a%20will%20was%20not%20about%20dying%2C%20but%20about%20finding%20ways%20to%20live%2C%20to%20love%2C%20and%20to%20share%20it%20with%20those%20who%20needed%20it.%20Isn't%20that%20what%20life%20should%20always%20be%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-married-no-children-kids-need-a-will-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1762510021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690ba0040be9845f2dc5cb8c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-married-no-children-kids-need-a-will-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I'm%20not%20married%20and%20I%20don't%20have%20kids%2C%20so%20I%20never%20felt%20the%20need%20to%20have%20a%20will.%20Now%20in%20my%2050s%2C%20I'm%20glad%20I%20know%20where%20my%20money%20is%20going%20when%20I'm%20gone.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Elana%20Rabinowitz)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-married-no-children-