5C%22440%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EChallenger%2C%20Gray%20%26amp%3B%20Christmas%20found%20that%20announced%20job%20cuts%20from%20US-based%20employers%20skyrocketed%20over%20the%20month%20to%20the%20highest%20October%20total%20since%202003%20%E2%80%94%20increasing%20from%2054%2C064%20to%20153%2C074%20this%20past%20October.%20Last%20month's%20gain%20means%20over%201%20million%20announced%20cuts%20so%20far%20this%20year%2C%20more%20than%20the%20roughly%20761%2C000%20cuts%20for%20the%20entire%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20industries%20are%20correcting%20after%20the%20hiring%20boom%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20but%20this%20comes%20as%20AI%20adoption%2C%20softening%20consumer%20and%20corporate%20spending%2C%20and%20rising%20costs%20drive%20belt-tightening%20and%20hiring%20freezes%2C%26quot%3B%20Andy%20Challenger%2C%20workplace%20expert%20and%20chief%20revenue%20officer%2C%20said%20in%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EErnie%20Tedeschi%2C%20a%20nonresident%20senior%20fellow%20at%20The%20Budget%20Lab%20at%20Yale%2C%20recently%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-one-chart-amazon-hiring-pandemic-great-resignation-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecompanies%20like%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20announced%20a%20reduction%20of%2014%2C000%20corporate%20workers%2C%20are%20likely%20correcting%20for%20overhiring%20during%20the%20pandemic-era%20and%20Great%20Resignation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221c1cd471-6910-4272-8dd0-0a203b8e4d11%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndeed%20found%20job%20opportunities%20are%20the%20lowest%20since%202021%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShrivastava%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20US%20is%20in%20a%20precarious%2C%20not%20dangerous%20situation%20based%20on%20the%20platform's%20data.%20Job%20postings%20trended%20downward%20last%20month%2C%20hitting%20the%20lowest%20point%20since%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThings%20have%20been%20kind%20of%20eroding%20slowly%2C%26quot%3B%20Shrivastava%20said.%20%26quot%3BNot%20a%20lot%20of%20job%20growth%20added%2C%20still%20really%20difficult%20to%20break%20into%20the%20labor%20market%2C%20people%20still%20really%20holding%20onto%20their%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flow-hire-low-fire-layoffs-employees-stuck-unemployment-job-seekers-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eemployees%20sitting%20still%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20Shrivastava%20said%20employers%20have%20mainly%20been%20holding%20onto%20workers.%20Despite%20new%20cuts%20making%20news%2C%20BLS%20data%20up%20to%20August%20showed%20US%20layoff%20rates%20have%20been%20low%20for%20years%20%E2%80%94%20the%202021%20to%202025%20average%20of%201.0%25%20is%20a%20hair%20below%20the%202015%20to%202019%20average%20of%201.2%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShrivastava%20said%20a%20surge%20in%20layoffs%20would%20%26quot%3Bbe%20kind%20of%20the%20thing%20that%20tips%20the%20tower%20over.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e7db21d3-f901-42db-b874-5c86fe9fdcf2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELinkedIn%20found%20hiring%20didn't%20change%20much%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKory%20Kantenga%2C%20the%20head%20of%20economics%20for%20the%20Americas%20at%20LinkedIn%2C%20said%20in%20a%20post%20that%20October%20hiring%20wasn't%20too%20far%20off%20from%20September%2C%20although%20it%20did%20fall%200.8%25%20and%20down%20from%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year.%20The%20number%20of%20job%20openings%20per%20applicant%20has%20also%20been%20cooling%2C%20and%20dropped%201%25%20over%20the%20month.%20Kantenga%20said%20in%20the%20post%20that%20both%20supply%20and%20demand%20have%20dropped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20job%20market%20has%20been%20running%20slow%2C%20it's%20continuing%20to%20run%20slow%2C%26quot%3B%20Kantenga%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThere%20just%20isn't%20a%20lot%20of%20momentum%20across%20the%20board.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKantenga%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20job%20seekers%20need%20to%20be%20open%20to%20industries%20that%20are%20still%20hiring%2C%20such%20as%20healthcare%20and%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20areas%20where%20things%20have%20actually%20started%20to%20turn%20around%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20yet%20where%20they%20need%20to%20be%20for%20there%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20opportunities%2C%26quot%3B%20Kantenga%20said.%20%26quot%3BTechnology%2C%20information%2C%20and%20media%20is%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228de53b36-a71c-48b4-923d-c5105d880487%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBank%20of%20America%20data%20showed%20pay%20growth%20varies%20by%20household%20income%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bank%20of%20America%20Institute%20said%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Bno%20significant%20further%20slowdown%20in%20the%20labor%20market%26quot%3B%20last%20month%20based%20on%20internal%20data%20on%20how%20many%20of%20the%20bank's%20customers%20are%20getting%20paychecks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20this%20data%20does%20suggest%20a%20slowdown%20in%20jobs%20growth%20has%20taken%20place%20since%20the%20summer%2C%20it%20tends%20to%20suggest%20that%20for%20now%20at%20least%2C%20there%20is%20no%20further%20deceleration%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20new%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnemployment%20payments%20were%20up%20from%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20but%20the%20report%20said%20the%20growth%20rate%20cooled%20slightly%20from%20September.%20Across%20the%20board%2C%20households%20had%20higher%20pay%20than%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20but%20higher-income%20households%20had%20the%20highest%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f38d747-9098-4021-ae67-c2441d4885b0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGusto%20found%20that%20small-business%20hiring%20has%20weakened%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGusto%2C%20a%20payroll%20and%20benefits%20platform%20for%20small%20businesses%2C%20found%20that%20the%20hiring%20rate%20and%20quits%20rate%20at%20those%20businesses%20cooled%20in%20October.%20Net%20hires%20at%20small%20businesses%20also%20fell%20by%205%2C900%2C%20the%20first%20drop%20since%20January.%20Average%20hourly%20earnings%20are%20also%20up%20a%20little%20bit%20from%20a%20year%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20witnessing%20a%20significant%20shift%20in%20small%20business%20hiring%20patterns%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrew%20Chamberlain%2C%20the%20principal%20economist%20at%20Gusto%2C%20said%2C%20adding%20there's%20essentially%20no%20job%20growth%20happening%20compared%20to%20the%20growth%20during%20the%20post-pandemic%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20culprits%20are%20clear%3A%20persistently%20high%20borrowing%20costs%20that%20keep%20business%20loans%20at%207-15%25%2C%20ongoing%20tariff%20uncertainty%20that%20makes%20planning%20nearly%20impossible%2C%20and%20elevated%20operating%20expenses%20across%20the%20board%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20rate%20cuts%20could%20help%20business%20owners.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-cuts-rates-25-basis-points-second-time-this-year-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFed%20cut%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20September%20and%20October%20after%20holding%20rates%20steady%20throughout%202025.%20Chamberlain%20said%20Gusto%20expects%20a%20rebound%20%26quot%3Bas%20the%20Fed%20starts%20to%20relax%20interest%20rates%20in%20the%20coming%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fno-jobs-report-alternative-data-labor-market-hiring-openings-layoffs-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1762508881000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690d138c21c3f142ebfc435e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fno-jobs-report-alternative-data-labor-market-hiring-openings-layoffs-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20won't%20be%20publishing%20the%20October%20jobs%20report%20on%